Definition: an examination conducted at regular intervals to determine whether a candidate is qualified to practice law in a given jurisdiction
Example: applicants may qualify to take the New York bar examination by graduating from an approved law school; he passed the bar exam on his third try
Synonyms: bar_exam, examination, an, conducted, at, regular, intervals, to, determine, whether, a, candidate, is, qualified, practice, law, in, given, jurisdiction, applicants, may, qualify, take, the, New, York, bar, by, graduating, from, approved, school, he, passed, exam, on, his, third, try
Category: noun.communication
